FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1775408752
OL,3,COne of world's tiniest antelopes born
OL,4,Cat Chester Zoo
OL,6,FDotty is being raised by mum Chrissy
OL,7,Fand with the help of surrogate father
OL,8,Fmale dik-dik Dan, who arrived from a
OL,9,Fzoo in Cumbria in February.
OL,11,FMegan Carpenter, Assistant Team
OL,12,FManager of Small Mammals at Chester
OL,13,FZoo, said: "Dik-diks are naturally
OL,14,Fvery shy animals, so for the first
OL,15,Fcouple of weeks Dotty has been tucked
OL,16,Faway in a quiet, cosy den, with mum
OL,17,Fpopping back to feed and check on her.
OL,18,FNow though, she's beginning to find
OL,19,Fher feet and we're seeing those lovely
OL,20,Ffirst steps as she heads out on her
OL,21,Ffirst little outdoor adventures.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1775408752
OL,3,COne of world's tiniest antelopes born
OL,4,Cat Chester Zoo
OL,6,F"In a lovely addition to the story,
OL,7,Fwe've also welcomed a new male dik-
OL,8,Fdik, Dan, as part of the European
OL,9,Fconservation breeding programme. He's
OL,10,Falready stepped in alongside mum
OL,11,FChrissy to help raise the newborn and
OL,12,Fit's wonderful to see the three of
OL,13,Fthem together."
OL,15,FThe species is often found in the
OL,16,Fscrublands and mountainous regions of
OL,17,FKenya, Tanzania and Namibia in Africa,
OL,18,Fwhere they take their name from the
OL,19,Fsharp, high-pitched "dik-dik" alarm
OL,20,Fcall they make when startled.
OL,26,@uD@OO]
